page.title: 05Housing In Reepham
page.content: In Reepham there are new houses and old houses.There are two quite new estates called Bircham Road and Moor House Park.Some of the houses have just been built and others are up to seven years old.There are no bunglows in Bircham Road and there is only one house which is semi detatched.Most people moved there because of the nice area for there children to play in.There are about forty to fifty detatched houses on Moor House Park. In and near the market place there are houses which have been there for over two hundred years.Going up Station Road some of the houses are about up to a hundred years old.Some are fifty years old.Then come the bunglows.Most ofthe oldest houses are near the market place,whilst most of the newest houses are on the edge of the town.
